19/20 CAPiTA Outerspace Living because who wouldn‚Äôt want one board that can do it all? The Outerspace is designed to cruise the mountain in its entirety with ease. Modeled after it‚Äôs big brother the #CAPiTAMercury, but with a true twin shape. This board works as well in the park as it does on the groomers and beyond. New for 19/20 we‚Äôve added Inlaid HD Titanal Struts integrated into the lightweight poplar and beech core for structural reinforcement, making this board a powerful, durable, and lightweight weapon with an extra boost. Also new for 19/20 the Outerspace Living series has adopted our SuperDrive‚Ñ¢ EX base, which is a combination of a sintered and extruded base, giving you the benefits of a fast sintered base without requiring you to spend the whole day waxing your board. Forgiving when you want it to be but strong enough to tackle sticky situations, take this board for a surf in the deep and when it gets tracked, hit the park. The Defenders of Awesome series has a big reputation and these boards back it up. As winners of the most coveted design award in snowboarding for an unprecedented seven years in a row, this highly sought-after series has won a Transworld Good Wood every single year of its existence. That's an undefeated record, folks! The DOA features a next-generation hybrid-camber design which delivers the pop and response of a cambered board with the predictability of reverse-camber. With construction technology like Fortress‚Ñ¢ Kevlar Bound Sidewalls and an all-new high-speed Quantum Drive‚Ñ¢ base advancing these boards beyond their modest retail price, the DOA series stands proud as the ultimate go anywhere, do anything freestyle deck. The Frontier‚Å†
‚Å†
The All-terrain, shred everything board. ‚Å†
‚Å†
Previously named the Explorer, the Frontier is a directional freeride board designed to be the perfect daily driver for the playful all-mountain shredder.‚Å†
‚Å†
Featuring a floaty, freeride nose matched with a freestyle tail, the Frontier is ideal for pow days, park days and every day in between. The Frontier‚Äôs Directional shape, Directional Rocker profile and Traction Tech 2.0 edges provide confident stability riding through tech terrain or rough snow while the spooned nose+tail edges on the 3D Contour Base 1.0 reduce edge catch and make it easy to turn in tight terrain. The Frontier offers high performance without skimping on materials as it‚Äôs built with a Sintered 7000 base, an Eco-plastic topsheet and a new FSC Classic Core that is specially profiled between the feet for added pop.‚Å†

We are super excited to finally check out SHELTER a new splitboard film featuring @matschaer & @jeremyjones‚Å£
‚Å£
How do you raise the bar AND lower your impact?‚Å£
‚Å£
That‚Äôs the challenge, SHELTER, a new backcountry shred movie by Almo Films and Picture Organic tackles head on.‚Å£
‚Å£
Shelter follows Mat Schaer, Jeremy Jones and friends as they tour between mountain huts in the Swiss, French and Italian Alps searching for epic riding terrain while producing a film with as little environmental impact possible.‚Å£
‚Å£
The film‚Äôs concept was inspired by Mat, a Swiss ripper who‚Äôs talents on a snowboard are only matched by his creativity and intelligence as an engineer and environmental activist. With his partners at Almo, Mat sought to produce a film that showcased groundbreaking snowboarding while inspiring real talk about how mountain explorers can adventure more sustainably and reduce the carbon footprint. SHELTER is their magnificent response to this challenge, a movie that pushes the limits of freestyle splitboarding using only public transportation and human power.‚Å£
‚Å£
Thrilled to present both the full movie and a captivating interview with Mat about highlights from filming and his inspiration for the project. Settle in, read on and watch this movie NOW!‚Å£

‚Å£
High Powered Body x Board Connection. ‚Å£
‚Å£
The Apollo binding is designed for the expert freerider who demands unmatched edge control, response and comfort. What sets the Apollo apart is the Jones‚Äô exclusive Flax/Carbon Highback that blends the ECO-performance of Flax with the lightweight, torsional stiffness of Carbon. Matching the premium highback with NOW Skate Tech technology created a binding that will respond to your every muscle twitch with lightning fast accuracy.‚Å£
‚Å£
The Mercury binding is designed for the all-mountain rider who needs supreme edge control and comfort balanced with a more maneuverable, medium stiff flex. The Mercury will respond instantly to your every move thanks to NOW Skate Tech technology that transfers your energy directly to your edges. The Mercury‚Äôs Flex Hinge highback offers solid support while absorbing chatter and eliminating calf-bite.‚Å£
‚Å£
Both bindings can be set up in Surf mode or Freeride mode by switching bushing and swapping the Flip-It ankle straps. Surf mode offers maximum tweak-ability, Freeride mode offers maximum response.‚Å£

üõ∏ I Heart Hovercrafting üõ∏ ‚Å£‚Å£ ‚Å£ 
Our original 2010 board line was a four board quiver - the Flagship, MTN Twin, Solution and Hovercraft. The black sheep of the line was undoubtedly the Hovercraft. With it‚Äôs big nose, wide waist width and squatty blunt tail the Hovercraft didn‚Äôt look anything like the other three models, nor anything like a traditional twin snowboard. So what did it look like? ‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
Back in 2010 there weren‚Äôt really words in the snowboard design vocabulary to describe what the Hovercraft looked like. To the simple eye, it was a powder board, which at that time was about the only thing a snowboard could be other than a freestyle board or a freeride board. But not to @jeremyjones , what Jeremy saw in the Hovercraft was an all-mountain, all-conditions game changer. What he didn‚Äôt know was how right he was.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
To celebrate the 10th anniversary of the Hovercraft, we wanted to take it back to the beginning and hear from our three original Hovercraft disciples @nick_russelll @forrestshearer @jeremyjones about why this board shape was an instantaneous success and arguably the most endearing shape we‚Äôve ever made. ‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£

"My first day riding the Hovercraft was in the Brighton side country. I was blown away. It was unlike anything I had ever ridden before. What I noticed was that I could ride it in deep pow and have this surfy, cruisy feeling and I could take it into the tracked out, choppy snow and feel just as stable and comfortable. The long sidecut lets you draw these big lines through big terrain, but the compact shape let‚Äôs you make these quick fluid motions in tight terrain. The Hovercraft ended up completely changing my riding style and adding a whole new element to my snowboarding. I haven‚Äôt looked back since." - @nick_russelll‚Å£
‚Å£
To celebrate a decade of the Hovercraft we put together a few stories, images and videos from the early days to present and dove into how this board has shaped a devout cult following. ‚Å£

‚ö†Ô∏èWelcome to the 10th Annual Jones Avalanche Awareness Month!‚ö†Ô∏è‚Å£
‚Å£
For the past decade we have kicked off the winter by asking backcountry riders of all abilities to refresh and improve their avalanche awareness skills. December is the perfect month for taking the time to focus on your avy and rescue skills as you‚Äôll use these skills the rest of the season.‚Å£
‚Å£
Snow totals have been piling up this past week across the globe and its now time to start getting in the right mind set before your first tour.  For us that starts with a simple gear check at home to make sure everything is still working properly, nothing broke over the summer and you have your pack ready to go knowing that everything is dialed for your first tour. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üõë BEACON/BATTERY CHECK: ‚Å£
Hopefully you took the batteries out of your beacon at the end of last season. It's time to put in some fresh ones and make sure to turn your beacon on, go through the functions and make sure everything is working. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üõëSHOVEL/PROBE CHECK: ‚Å£
Nothing worse than having a broken shovel or probe when you need it the most. A quick check that both your shovel and probe connect, extend and lock makes starting the year out feeling good that your gear is solid. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üõëFIRST AID/MED/SUPPLY KIT: ‚Å£
A quick run through and reevaluation of your basic med kit, restock any supplies, add anything new. Check GPS/In Reach devices make sure they are working. If don't have any of these and regularly travel in the backcountry might be time to think about investing in both. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üõëCHECK AVY REPORT: ‚Å£
It's time to get back in that avalanche mind set. Set up email or text alerts from your local Avy center, be sure to follow them on social media for real time up dates and starting making that daily report check a part of your morning routine. ‚Å£
‚Å£
üõë SIGN UP FOR AVY CLASS: ‚Å£
If you have never taken one now is the perfect time! If you have experience look into a refresher course or get out and start practicing with your partners. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Just a few basic things you can do at home to starting getting ready for the year!

The Apollo binding is designed for the expert freerider who demands unmatched edge control, response and comfort. What sets the Apollo apart is the Jones‚Äô exclusive Flax/Carbon Highback that blends the ECO-performance of Flax with the lightweight, torsional stiffness of Carbon. Matching the premium highback with NOW Skate Tech technology created a binding that will respond to your every muscle twitch with lightning fast accuracy.‚Å£

The Mercury binding is designed for the all-mountain rider who needs supreme edge control and comfort balanced with a more maneuverable, medium stiff flex. The Mercury will respond instantly to your every move thanks to NOW Skate Tech technology that transfers your energy directly to your edges. The Mercury‚Äôs Flex Hinge highback offers solid support while absorbing chatter and eliminating calf-bite.‚Å£
‚Å£
Both bindings can be set up in Surf mode or Freeride mode by switching bushing and swapping the Flip-It ankle straps. Surf mode offers maximum tweak-ability, Freeride mode offers maximum response.‚Å£

I spy a....GIVEAWAY ALERT! Stop what you're doing; drop your lunch, coffee, beer and or kid and WIN @ejackshreds gear! We're teaming up with Eric Ôºã @spyoptic to give ONE lucky winner a pair of the new EJack signature Legacy Snow Goggles and an #EjackKnife board! To enter, follow @spyoptic, @ejackshreds Ôºã @libtechnologies, and tag two friends in the comments below. Winner announced tomorrow!!! Tomorrow? Yes, tomorrow!! This is time sensitive people!!! Why are we yelling?!?Why aren't you?!?!!? #libtech #mervinmade

@reis_the_beast get's a dream trick on his #ReisBanana to close out his full part playing now at lib-tech.com, link in bio. Happy New Year! Time with friends is time well spent and snowboarding with them is food for the soul. May this year be your best yet! @austensweetin and @travisrice @stellarheli on the #libXlost Rocket and #TriceOrca #libtech #mervinmade #RoadToHolyBowly  Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

@travisrice preys upon unsuspecting terrain with his #TriceOrca. New sizes at your local shop use our Locally button to connect to a retailer near you. That Ôºã vid Ôºã more at lib-tech.com, link in bio! @stellarheli #libtech #mervinmade Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram
Winter has truly landed in the NW and @austensweetin was right where he needed to be with some #libtech dream boards @therealmtbakerskiarea. #mcwayfinder #triceorca #mervinmade

The #TriceOrca! @travisrice's apex predator, powder hunting, freeride focused ab-so-lute RIPPER now available at your local shop in three MORE NEW SIZES; 144cm, 150cm and 156cm! Use our locally feature to connect to a retailer holdin' whale tail near you.
This year's Orca art is another amazing piece by @kim_krans - ‚ÄúTrue to its name, this board is an epic tribute to the force of the Orca. I used a super traditional pointalism technique to create the gradation of the whale‚Äôs body, and we let all the magic come from its single eye. The idea here is that this board carries you through the depths of the backcountry, and the Orca‚Äôs eye is your compass along the way. There is no getting lost‚Äù ~ Kim Krans
Find board dims Ôºã Locally shop finder Ôºã Orca video Ôºã teaser for Trav's new Dark Matter project all up now at lib-tech.com, link in bio.#libtech #mervinmade @stellarheli Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram
@travisrice relies on the gold standard of "sending it" the #triceGoldmember. #libtech #mervinmade pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram
@ejackshreds enjoying a pow platter on the #EjackKnife. #libtech #mervinmade Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram
Santa is acting a little weird....but he's ripping on that #EjackKnife! @ejackshreds #libtech #MervinMade in the USA. See more at lib-tech.com Vid: @lucey Song: @robigonz

The #libtechMagicBM! Lib co-founder #MikeOlson took everything he has learned about board design in the past 40 years and created his dream board, the Magic BM. Founded on a dynamic ‚Äúenhanced banana‚Äù C2 contour the BM floats effortlessly in powder with a very smooth riding low entry directional nose shape. It's perfectly tuned cambers and deep sidecuts combine with the radical central rocker to set up incredible edge hold and carving on hard pack making this one magically fun, dreamy, high performance board. Add in a tip to tail banger of a @q_quigg graphic and a checker board base and you guessed, instant classic wall hanger that also SHREDS like no other! Ask @n0t_matteo, he loves this board, pictured here at #holybowly letting the hoof breath, it's just that easy. #libtech #mervinmade #RoadToHolyBowly Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

We got out to @stubai_glacier yesterday for some mid @mervinmfg sales meeting shred. For dec 4th it was üëåüëåüëåüëåTimes were had! @hedbergmans @frederik_kalbermatten @jesseburtner @barrettcc #totalripperseries #libtechswissknife #libtechdynamiss #boxscratcher #libtech #mervinmade
Back three up close and in deep with @austensweetin from "Rooster Tail" playing now at lib-tech.com, link in bio. #libtech #LibTechDynamo #MervinMade #RoadToHolyBowly vid: @lucey

@jamiemlynn's #TittyFish!  Jamie Lynn is in constant motion: progressing as a human, pushing his skateboarding, art and snowboarding to new levels. The Titty Fish is Jamie‚Äôs dream power freestyle stick built for aggressive, no limits, straight to the point snowboarding. A powerful flex, aggressive camber and stable open speed friendly sidecut. Big floaty nose that planes effortlessly and a tapered shape that settles nicely in soft snow for big landings and straight line run outs. Featuring an instant classic Jamie painting in beautiful black and white. Pic: @blairhabenicht by @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram #libtech #mervinmade

@travisrice navigates a dream line @stellarheli on his dream board the #TriceOrca. Check Orca vids and find one at shop near you using our Locally feature at lib-tech.com. #libtech #mervinmade Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

Attention ALL, we're hiring! Join the Mervin Mfg. board building family in Sequim, WA. Become a part of the decades long legacy of board building that started with Mike Olson and Pete Saari and continues today with a vibrant community of craftsmen, ripper, artist, personalities who are building zero hazardous waste DREAM boards for the entire world. Including world class Olympic athletes and larger than life action heros like @jamiemlynn, @travisrice and @jamieanderson and way more! @mervinmfg we have killer benefits, a four day work week, yearly free board of your choice, incentives to shred and just recently an across the board raise! Scroll over to see more details or just go straight to mervin.com/careers We are in for life doing this thing! Handcrafted in the USA for real, Zero Hazardous Waste for real,  dream boards for real! Come join us!  @mervinmfg #LibTech #MervinMade

The #TriceGoldMember! @travisrice worked with our experiMENTAL Division to design this dream freestyling directional freerider. Ultra light, smooth riding basalt construction that can handle power and an oversized terrain mindset. Low spin weight tips and tails and a balsa enlightened core for nimble precision and extra rotations where applicable. Dream big!
The art in Travis' entire line this season was done by @kim_krans), artist, author, and creator of The New York Times bestseller, The Wild Unknown Tarot. ‚ÄúWith the Goldmember we were looking to create a crystalline light force meant to help the rider blaze their own trail. We kept it super simple and clean with nuanced details in the linework and color. It‚Äôs basically like riding on top of a meditative light vortex... it‚Äôs for those looking to elevate to the next level, or as Travis put it, experience a ‚Äúspark of awakening.‚Äù ~ Kim Krans
Check out more Gold Member at lib-tech.com! #libtech #mervinmade

A good angle of the @kim_krans "meditative light vortex" on the #libtechgoldmember top sheet. Looks like it's just the "spark of awakening" Phil needed for this cranked out method at #BowlyDownUnder. @nutrash_hansen @travisrice #LibTech #MervinMade #RoadToHolyBowly
Dream boards for dream days. @blairhabenicht scores @therealmtbakerskiarea on the #LibTech #TittyFish. #MervinMade #RoadToHolyBowly Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

@austensweetin has done it again! ‚ÄúRooster Tail‚Äù a high speed full on powder freestyle assault, link in bio! Robble robble full throbble! Vid: @lucey #libtech #libtechdynamo #mervinmade #roadtoholybowly
Dream boards on a dream day. #LibTechDynamo Ôºã #Tittyfish see more at lib-tech.com #libtech #mervinmade @blairhabenicht @austensweetin @stellarheli Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

When it comes to big backcountry freestyle moments over icy chasms @travisrice looks to his #TriceGoldmember. A C2 perfection chasis with ultra light, smooth riding basalt and balsa enlightened construction that can handle power and an oversized terrain mindset. Check the Goldmember vid at lib-tech.com! #libtech #mervinmade Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

The iconic #SkateBanana as interperted by @reis_the_beast , introducing the #ReisBanana! We invited one of snowboarding‚Äôs most prolific freestyle rulers, Brandon Reis, to reimagine the vibe of the iconic Skate Banana. We gave him a blank canvas and free reign to unleash his @monareisa drawings on his favorite all mountain board. And that he did. Brandon went full ‚Äúkid brain‚Äù on it creating the most unique Skate Banana we‚Äôve ever had, a new look at the board that turned snowboarding upside down by a guy who loves going upside down, perfect! Brandon rides his Banana everywhere, from The House of Reis (his backyard) to the variable slopes and parks of his native New Hampshire to Holy Bowly, Mt. Baker, the streets of Oslo and everywhere in between. Sean Lucey and the MMMedia squad put together a sick Reis Banana part with a bushell of bangers and unseen stunts, link in bio! #libtech #mervinmade #RoadToHolyBowly Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

The #libtechMagicBM! Lib co-founder #MikeOlson took everything he has learned about board design in the past 40 years and created his dream board, the Magic BM. Founded on a dynamic ‚Äúenhanced banana‚Äù C2 contour the BM floats effortlessly in powder with a very smooth riding low entry directional nose shape. It's perfectly tuned cambers and deep sidecuts combine with the radical central rocker to set up incredible edge hold and carving on hard pack making this one magically fun, dreamy, high performance board. Add in a tip to tail banger of a @q_quigg graphic and a checker board base and you guessed, instant classic wall hanger that also SHREDS like no other! Ask @n0t_matteo, he loves this board, pictured here at #holybowly letting the hoof breath, it's just that easy. #libtech #mervinmade #RoadToHolyBowly Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram

The iconic #SkateBanana as interperted by @reis_the_beast , introducing the #ReisBanana! We invited one of snowboarding‚Äôs most prolific freestyle rulers, Brandon Reis, to reimagine the vibe of the iconic Skate Banana. We gave him a blank canvas and free reign to unleash his @monareisa drawings on his favorite all mountain board. And that he did. Brandon went full ‚Äúkid brain‚Äù on it creating the most unique Skate Banana we‚Äôve ever had, a new look at the board that turned snowboarding upside down by a guy who loves going upside down, perfect! Brandon rides his Banana everywhere, from The House of Reis (his backyard) to the variable slopes and parks of his native New Hampshire to Holy Bowly, Mt. Baker, the streets of Oslo and everywhere in between. Sean Lucey and the MMMedia squad put together a sick Reis Banana part with a bushell of bangers and unseen stunts, link in bio! #libtech #mervinmade #RoadToHolyBowly Pic: @fotomaxizoomdweebie #zimstagram
